[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Welcome. Today we\'re looking at the plug-in features for Ace Studio. Ace Studio can support third-party VST and AU effects plugins. Currently, as of 2.1.2, this is limited to effects only, but we'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'will soon update to include instrument plugins as well. So, let\'s look at how to add a third-party plugin or any plugin onto the track. So, you can always hover over the track'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'icon and click on the effects. Alternatively, you can go to the mixer by clicking this icon or hitting M and going through and hitting effects button over here.'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, say I want to add some effects on the drums. This is what it sounds like. I can click on the effects icon and already have a few effects on here.'

[00:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Uh maybe I want to add a little reverb. So, I can click on insert and I can search all my third-party effects just through these categories over here. You can also search by brands.'

[01:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Uh I\'m going to add a slight reverb. Uh maybe uh plate reverb. And now you see your your third-party plugin window pop up right here. Now, if you ever want to close it, you'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can just click on X. If you want to pull it up again, you can click on this icon over here. If you ever need to disable it, we can just turn it off over here by clicking this icon over here.'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now, now that we added a little reverb, &gt;&gt; [snorts] &gt;&gt; All right, so I have a little bit of slight reverb going on.'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; Okay. Now, say I\'m really happy with this effects chain and I want to reuse it. Now, what you can do is just'

[01:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'highlight shift and click to highlight all your effects in the effects chain and I can right click and save your entire effects chain. So this saves everything as a as a'

[02:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'effects chain preset that you can use. Now, if I ever want to use this same effects chain again, all I have to do is when I hit insert, I can go to effects chain and I can'

[02:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'click on and it\'ll pull up all the effects saved right there for you. Now, it\'s also really easy to reorder effects. You can just click it and move'

[02:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it around, changing the signal flow of the effects chain. The master track also has an effects as well, so you can add things that affect your entire mix right here. If you don\'t see your third-party'

[02:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'plugins, you can always go to preferences and go to plugins and you can rescan your entire plugin folder.'

[02:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If you ever need to do a deep scan, maybe you have a few plugins that might be disabled or are broken, you can hold down option and hit rescan and it\'ll do a deep scan of your plugin folder.'

[03:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So third-party plugins gives us a lot more mixing and sound design possibilities right into FL Studio. Keep following us for more tips, tricks, and tutorials. See you soon.'

[03:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Bye.'
